<TITLE> JS sees UGC recommendations against sexual harassment of students </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com)  The education minister Nurul Islam Nahid presented the University Grants Commission's recommendations to prevent sexual harassment in educational institutions in parliament on Wednesday. The UGC made the recommendations to the government in its 34th annual report. The The apex body of the university system also expressed worries about suicidal deaths of university stduents and recommended. The report also stated that the admission process of private universiies should be made more transparent and merit-oriented. The UGC recommended a joint partnership be made between industries and academia to realise innovations in the field of education including information and communication technology. The body also suggested formulating policies to monitor activities of the academic, administrative and conducting committees of all colleges, which represent around 80 percent of students under the National University. bdnew
